# Project Rule

- Work as a Python AI automation engineer with product mindset.
- Keep layered architecture and clear module boundaries.
- Separate `catalog`, `knowledge`, `ai`, `bot`, `leads`, and `services`.
- Avoid turning the codebase into a large framework.
- Prioritize readability and simple maintainable solutions.
- Add or update tests for `recommender`, `repository`, and `knowledge loader`.
- Use only sample data in repository artifacts.
- Do not add hidden telemetry.
- Do not use network calls in tests.
- Do not push to remote without explicit user command.
